29 Huff recorded 16 kills; and
30 WHEREAS, in addition to Catherine McClain being named
31 Tournament MVP, three other players, Bella Smith, Alice
32 Wood, and Cami Huff, earned selection to the Class 7A Elite
33 8 All-Tournament Team; and
34 WHEREAS, the McGill-Toolen Dirty Dozen has been
35 superbly coached and inspired by Head Coach Kate Wood, who
36 has led the program since 2014, guiding the team to six
37 state championships and earning recognition as the NFHS
38 Alabama Coach of the Year in 2024; and
39 WHEREAS, under Coach Wood's leadership, and with the
40 support of assistant coaches Laura Johnson and Samantha
41 Nichols, the program has sustained a tradition of excellence
42 while emphasizing player development, producing multiple
43 Gatorade Players of the Year and AVCA All-Americans,
44 including current standout Alice Wood, who is also the
45 daughter of Coach Wood; and
46 WHEREAS, the 2025 Championship Varsity Volleyball
47 roster includes players Emmy Beech, Taylor Brown, Camille
48 Fromdahl, Hannah Hodges, Cami Huff, Makayla Johnson, Jaedyn
49 Lang, Emmy Littrell, Catherine McClain, Payton McClarren,
50 Caitlin Miller, Teagan O'Brien, Evie Rice, Bella Smith,
51 Rowan Thompson, and Alice Wood; now therefore,
52 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
53 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That the McGill-Toolen Catholic
54 High School Varsity Volleyball Team is hereby highly
55 commended and congratulated for winning its fourth
56 consecutive AHSAA Class 7A State Championship, and this
